	<p>"The Displaced Persons Olympiad" was not the only and not the first celebration of the "Olympic spirit" in the camps. In 1944 the XIII Olympic Games were supposed to take place in London, but were moved to 1948 because of the war. The International Olympic Committee still organized several anniversary celebrations in the Swiss city of Lausanne. As became known after the war, during the summer of 1944 the XIII Olympic Games were also remembered in two camps for Polish prisoners of war on the territory of Germany: in the villages of Gross Born and Woldenberg. The prisoners created a series of handmade stamps and postcards dedicated to the Olympics that did not take place.</p>

	<h4>Physically Prepared – And so, Armed!</h4>
	<div class="text_carousel slide">
            <div class="carousel-inner">
